content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: --ENDTC
      operator: non_empty
    - name: --DTC
      operator: non_empty
    - name: --DTC
      operator: date_greater_than
      value: --ENDTC
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.58
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: Raise and error when --ENDTC before --DTC
Outcome:
  Message: --ENDTC must be greater than or equal to --DTC
  Output Variables:
    - --ENDTC
    - --DTC
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '58'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: If both --DTC and --ENDTC are collected, durations
                  can be calculated by the difference in these two values...
                Document: IG v3.1
                Section: 4.4.3
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - ALL
  Domains:
    Include:
      - ALL

Outcome.Message: --ENDTC must be greater than or equal to --DTC

Citations.Cited_Guidance: If both --DTC and --ENDTC are collected, durations can be calculated by the difference in these two values...
